static4.businessinsider.com/image/590b4e57fcd8eb1b008b5075-857/screen%20shot%202015-09-14%20at%2083455%20am.png" alt="hiking" data-mce-source="Rick McCharles/Flickr" data-mce-caption="Hiking to Choquequirao, Peru." data-link="https://www.flickr.com/photos/rickmccharles/160043012/in/photolist-f9gdh-r7yEEr-qaGYx7-qPPHkV-tCyPqK-rouZRr-ody49h-obFgkS-nXpVho-qnhB6Z-bmvWHm-qJCatJ-qQ41kd-jqJX8B-raDgKt-r7xGay-r7jccT-qPMF4r-tYY8n6-rqCVYj-sg3SEB-tCre1Y-r4RS9C-xjA7a9-qjeA9i-oDTKx7-jqK4TR-o7JG4P-hNrSh-xYH3qG-rrZavS-qRp7wV-r7HC6p-9mDx4E-rLZYBr-r3qiSd-qQ3Acd-r5iEs9-r7vVaL-y19Hr7-qRq2XT-nWdGns-eTcdQ4-viM331-snvJ2q-rrZBfY-rrYfyt-ravpsN-ravWby-r1BvNK"><span class="caption-source"><span class='caption'>It's easier than you think to build travel into your permanent budget. (The Money Wizard is not pictured).</span><span class="source"><span><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/rickmccharles/160043012/in/photolist-f9gdh-r7yEEr-qaGYx7-qPPHkV-tCyPqK-rouZRr-ody49h-obFgkS-nXpVho-qnhB6Z-bmvWHm-qJCatJ-qQ41kd-jqJX8B-raDgKt-r7xGay-r7jccT-qPMF4r-tYY8n6-rqCVYj-sg3SEB-tCre1Y-r4RS9C-xjA7a9-qjeA9i-oDTKx7-jqK4TR-o7JG4P-hNrSh-xYH3qG-rrZavS-qRp7wV-r7HC6p-9mDx4E-rLZYBr-r3qiSd-qQ3Acd-r5iEs9-r7vVaL-y19Hr7-qRq2XT-nWdGns-eTcdQ4-viM331-snvJ2q-rrZBfY-rrYfyt-ravpsN-ravWby-r1BvNK">Rick McCharles/Flickr</a></span></span></span></span><p></span></span>By the time he was 16, the blogger behind <a href="http://mymoneywizard.com/">the Money Wizard</a> — who goes by the pen name Sean online — had already started saving for retirement.</p> <p>More than 10 years later and the 27-year-old's <a href="http://mymoneywizard.com/net-worth/">net worth is $170,500 and counting</a>. It's all part of a <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/early-retirement-playbook-from-26-year-old-2016-9">plan to retire by age 37</a>, but he's not depriving himself to get there, he says.</p> <p>He's currently earning a salary of $80,000 as a financial analyst in Minneapolis and saving about 65% of his take-home pay to contribute to his 401(k), IRA, and index funds. Still, thanks to smart spending habits, Sean says he lives comfortably and travels at least once a month.</p> <p>In 2016, he took a dozen round-trip flights in the US, which included skiing in Lake Tahoe and Utah, a weekend trip to Cape Cod, and a summer national park trip out West.</p> <p>Below, the Money Wizard shares with Business Insider his best tips for saving money on travel.</p> <div class="slideshow-content slide-intro-bottom"> <h4> View As: <a href="#" onclick="return false;" class="sl-start border-right disabled">One Page</a> <a href="http://www.businessinsider.com/millennial-super-saver-shares-7-best-tips-for-traveling-on-a-budget-2017-5?op=0#/#1-fly-on-slower-travel-days-1" class="sl-start href-swap">Slides</a> </h4> </div> <div class="clearfix"></div> </div> <br class="clear-both" /> <script type="text/javascript"> BI.vaop = []; </script> <!-- Slides --> <!-- add the slide content to the slide html object --> <div data-slide="1" id="1-fly-on-slower-travel-days-1" class="slide-module first-slide clearfix vaop-breakpoint"> <!-- add title if exists --> <h3 class="slide-title">1. Fly on slower travel days</h3> <div class="KonaFilter image-container slide-image-large on-image"><div><img data-src="http://static6.businessinsider.com/image/590b5c92fcd8eb20008b511c-1200/1-fly-on-slower-travel-days.jpg" src="/assets/images/logos/BI-placeholder.svg" alt="1. Fly on slower travel days" border="0" class="slide-image-large on-image" /></div><span class="caption-source"><span class="caption">Flying a slow travel day will save you on money and stress.</span><span><span class="source"><span><a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/irishflyguy/2436838012">Flickr/Christopher Doyle</a></span></span></span></span></div> <p>There's a reason you've heard this advice ad infinitum: It's nearly foolproof.</p> <p>"If possible, I arrange my vacations around the cheapest days of the week to fly — <span data-term="goog_1912503932">Tuesday through Thursday and Saturday," Sean said. "Choosing to fly on these slower travel days often saves up to 50% on tickets, compared to the usual Monday, Friday, Sunday travel times. Comparison websites like <a href="https://www.google.com/flights/">Google Flights</a> are my favorite for quickly comparing the cost differences between travel days and airlines."</span></p> </div> <script type="text/javascript"> var curSlideObj = {}; curSlideObj.title = "1. Fly on slower travel days"; curSlideObj.postTitle = "A 27-year-old who saves 65% of his income shares his 7 best tips for traveling on a budget"; curSlideObj.url = "http://www.businessinsider.com/millennial-super-saver-shares-7-best-tips-for-traveling-on-a-budget-2017-5/#1-fly-on-slower-travel-days-1"; curSlideObj.anchor = "1-fly-on-slower-travel-days-1"; curSlideObj.index = 0; curSlideObj.embeds = {}; curSlideObj.slideShareButtonsEnabled = true; curSlideObj.name ="/#1-fly-on-slower-travel-days-1";curSlideObj.embeds =[];curSlideObj.html ="";curSlideObj.ads =""; BI.vaop.push(curSlideObj); </script> <!-- add the slide content to the slide html object --> <div data-slide="2" id="2-build-travel-into-your-budget-2" class="slide-module clearfix vaop-breakpoint"> <!-- add title if exists --> <h3 class="slide-title">2. Build travel into your budget</h3> <p>Travel is important to Sean, so he's cut down fixed expenses to make vacationing a part of his permanent budget. "Far and away the easiest way to budget for travel is to save money without trying," he said.</p> <p>"Choosing an apartment with rent a couple hundred dollars cheaper is enough to fund a round trip plane ticket once a month. In 2016, the average car payment was $503 per month — that's nearly enough for a week of hotel stays."</p> </div> <script type="text/javascript"> var curSlideObj = {}; curSlideObj.title = "2. Build travel into your budget"; curSlideObj.postTitle = "A 27-year-old who saves 65% of his income shares his 7 best tips for traveling on a budget"; curSlideObj.url = "http://www.businessinsider.com/millennial-super-saver-shares-7-best-tips-for-traveling-on-a-budget-2017-5/#2-build-travel-into-your-budget-2"; curSlideObj.anchor = "2-build-travel-into-your-budget-2"; curSlideObj.index = 1; curSlideObj.embeds = {}; curSlideObj.slideShareButtonsEnabled = true; curSlideObj.name ="/#2-build-travel-into-your-budget-2";curSlideObj.embeds =[];curSlideObj.html ="";curSlideObj.ads ="
